.TH "restrict_link_reject" 9 "restrict_link_reject" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
restrict_link_reject \- Give -EPERM to restrict link
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" restrict_link_reject
.BI "(struct key *keyring "  ","
.BI "const struct key_type *type "  ","
.BI "const union key_payload *payload "  ","
.BI "struct key *restriction_key "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "keyring" 12
The keyring being added to.
.IP "type" 12
The type of key being added.
.IP "payload" 12
The payload of the key intended to be added.
.IP "restriction_key" 12
Keys providing additional data for evaluating restriction.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Reject the addition of any links to a keyring.  It can be overridden by
passing KEY_ALLOC_BYPASS_RESTRICTION to \fBkey_instantiate_and_link\fP when
adding a key to a keyring.

This is meant to be stored in a key_restriction structure which is passed
in the restrict_link parameter to \fBkeyring_alloc\fP.
